description:
Ecoregions were originally designated by the U.S. Forest Service in 1978 to provide a general description of the ecosystem geography of the United States. Prepared by the U.S. Forest Service in February 2000. Reprojected to UTM83 by WVGISTC.

Domain, division, province, and section as determined by vegetation and climate characteristics.
